com.samsung.android.sdk.healthdata

Interface HealthConstants.FoodIntake

  • All Superinterfaces:
    HealthConstants.Common, HealthConstants.DiscreteMeasurement
    Enclosing class:
    HealthConstants

    public static interface HealthConstants.FoodIntake
extends HealthConstants.DiscreteMeasurement
    This interface defines food intake data of user.

    Properties of the following extending interfaces are available for this data type.

    • HealthConstants.Common
    • HealthConstants.DiscreteMeasurement

    FoodIntake and FoodInfo

    Saved FoodIntake data's nutritional information is related with FoodInfo data.
    You can link FoodIntake and FoodInfo data by setting FoodIntake.FOOD_INFO_ID with FoodInfo.UUID and display your food intake data's nutritional info on S Health. 

       FoodIntake.FOOD_INFO_ID <- FoodInfo.UUID
    Otherwise, your saved food intake data are not shown properly on S Health.

    Properties

    Food intake data has the following properties.
    See more common properties by spreading this section out.

      Property name Description
      HealthConstants.FoodIntake.UUID [Mandatory]
      Data's unique ID,
      assigned by the system when new data is inserted
      HealthConstants.FoodIntake.CREATE_TIME [Mandatory]
      Data's created time in the health data store,
      assigned by the system when new data is inserted
      HealthConstants.FoodIntake.UPDATE_TIME [Mandatory]
      Data's updated time in the health data store,
      assigned by the system when new data is updated
      HealthConstants.FoodIntake.PACKAGE_NAME [Mandatory]
      Application package name which provides data,
      assigned by the system when new data is inserted
      HealthConstants.FoodIntake.DEVICE_UUID [Mandatory]
      Device identifier of the source device which provides health data
      HealthConstants.FoodIntake.START_TIME [Mandatory]
      UTC Time when the measurement is started
      HealthConstants.FoodIntake.TIME_OFFSET [Mandatory]
      Time offset which considers time zone and daylight saving time
      HealthConstants.FoodIntake.CALORIE [Mandatory]
      Total calories of the meal
      HealthConstants.FoodIntake.FOOD_INFO_ID Food information ID
      HealthConstants.FoodIntake.AMOUNT Count of food intake
      HealthConstants.FoodIntake.UNIT Unit used to describe the meal quantity
      HealthConstants.FoodIntake.NAME Name given to the meal
      HealthConstants.FoodIntake.MEAL_TYPE Meal type
      HealthConstants.FoodIntake.COMMENT Comment

    Data Permission

    Data permission acquisition for this data type is required toread or write data.
    See Permission Manager and request data permission.

    • Field Detail

      • FOOD_INFO_ID

        static final String FOOD_INFO_ID
        Food information ID.

        If you want to show nutritional information of food intake in S Health, set this property with UUID of HealthConstants.FoodInfo.
        If there is no defined food info for food intake, define its food info and insert.

        You can refer to the FoodNote sample application in the downloaded SDK.

        • Optional
        • Type: String
        • Value length: 10 ~ 32

        Since:
        1.0.0
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • CALORIE

        static final String CALORIE
        Total calories of the meal in kilocalories.

        • Mandatory
        • Type: float
        • Value range: 0 ~ 99999

        Setting Food Intake's Calories

        Calories on S Health's food tracker are calculated as shown below.

           CALORIE = FoodInfo.CALORIE / FoodInfo.METRIC_SERVING_AMOUNT * FoodIntake.AMOUNT

        1.0.0
